    "number": 34723,
    "state": "open",
    "state_reason": null,
    "title": "macOS + REDUCE_EXPORTS: Cap'n Proto misidentifies kj::Exception as unknown non-KJ exception",
    "body": "macOS builds with `REDUCE_EXPORTS` currently cause Cap'n Proto RPC to report:\n\n```c++\nremote exception: unknown non-KJ exception of type: kj::Exception\n```\n\ninstead of expected typed exception messages. Tests currently contain a [workaround](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/bf9ef4f0433551e850a11c2da8baae0ec6439a99/test/functional/interface_ipc_mining.py#L316-L321) to accept this behavior.\n\nThis issue tracks investigating and fixing the underlying exception type visibility/RTTI problem and removing the workaround.\n\nRelated: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34422#discussion_r2863852691",
